{
  "texts": [
    "For the healthy data, integration was done using all common genes and the first 30 principal components.",
    "For integration of all samples, the top 3,000 variable genes from the healthy, regenerating and embolized samples, as well as the top 100 marker genes from each cell type identified in the healthy dataset were selected.",
    "These were used to do a PCA on the full data, of which the top 50 principal components were used.",
    "The genes considered allowed a coverage of the biological variability in all conditions and present populations, despite the unbalanced representation of cell types in each sequenced fraction (Hepatocytes and Nonparenchymal cells).",
    "Dimensionality reduction, clustering, and annotation of singlecell data."
  ]
}